standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l4, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L4",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 4: Does the Number Change?. The purpose of this lesson is for students to count collections of objects and understand that the number of objects in a collection stays the same, regardless of how they are arranged. Goals: Generalize (orally) that the number of objects in a group is unchanged when the objects are rearranged or counted in a different way.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l5, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L5",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 5: How Many Fingers? How Many Dots?. The purpose of this lesson is for students to count to answer “how many?” questions about groups of up to 19 images. Goals: Identify (orally) written numbers 11–20. | Match (orally) images and written numbers that represent the same value within 20.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l6, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L6",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 6: Fingers and 10-Frames. The purpose of this lesson is for students to represent numbers 11–19 with fingers and on a 10-frame. Goals: Determine (orally) the number of fingers shown in an image with 10 fingers and some more fingers. Represent that number with 10-frames.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l7, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L7",
