standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l8, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L8",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 8: Make Numbers with 10 and Some More (Part 2). The purpose of this lesson is for students to compose numbers 11–19 using 10 ones and some more ones. Goals: Use 10-frames to represent numbers 11–19.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l9, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L9",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 9: Expressions and Equations. The purpose of this lesson is for students to make sense of expressions and equations that represent numbers 11–19. Goals: Match (orally) equations and images of 10-frames that represent the same relationships. | Match (orally) expressions and numbers that represent the same value.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l10, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L10",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 10: Complete Equations. The purpose of this lesson is for students to represent numbers 11–19 with equations. Goals: Use equations to represent numbers 11–19 as a sum of 10 and some more ones.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l11, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L11",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 11: Count Images (Part 1). The purpose of this lesson is for students to use the 10 ones and some more ones structure of numbers 11–19 to help them count groups of up to 19 images. Goals: Decompose a number represented by a group of images into a group of 10 and some more ones. Represent the total with a written number.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l12, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L12",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 12: Count Images (Part 2). The purpose of this lesson is for students to count to answer “how many?” questions about groups of up to 20 images and keep track of images that have been counted. Goals: Determine (orally) the number of images arranged in a circle.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u6_l13, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U6-L13",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 6 Lesson 13: Design a Garden. The purpose of this lesson is for students to draw groups of up to 20 images in the context of arranging vegetables in a garden. Goals: Create or draw a collection that represents a real- world context. | Write numbers to represent a quantity.").
