standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u7_l9, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U7-L9",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 7 Lesson 9: Compare Capacities. The purpose of this lesson is to introduce students to the concept and language used to compare capacities. Goals: Use the words “less” and “more” to compare (orally) the capacity of 2 objects.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u7_l10, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U7-L10",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 7 Lesson 10: Identify and Describe Solid Shapes. The purpose of this lesson is for students to identify and describe solid shapes. Goals: Identify (orally) a sphere, a cylinder, a cube, and a cone in known objects in the environment. | Represent a sphere, a cylinder, a cube, and a cone with clay.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u7_l11, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U7-L11",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 7 Lesson 11: Compare and Sort Solid Shapes. The purpose of this lesson is for students to compare solid shapes. Goals: Compare and contrast (orally) solid shapes, using informal language. | Describe (orally) the attributes of solid shapes, using informal language.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u7_l12, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U7-L12",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 7 Lesson 12: Build Solid Shapes. The purpose of this lesson is for students to build solid shapes from components. Goals: Represent rectangular prisms with connecting cubes. | Represent solid shapes with sticks and clay.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u7_l13, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U7-L13",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 7 Lesson 13: Describe Solid Shapes around Us. The purpose of this lesson is for students to notice and describe the locations of solid shapes in their environment. Goals: Describe (orally) examples of solid shapes in the environment, including using positional words. | Represent solid shapes in the environment with clay.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u7_l14, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U7-L14",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 7 Lesson 14: Build with Solid Shapes. The purpose of this lesson is for students to compose solid shapes to build new shapes. Goals: Describe (orally) objects composed of solid shapes, including using positional words.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u7_l15, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U7-L15",
