standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l1, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L1",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 1: Sort, Count, and Compare Groups of Objects. The purpose of this lesson is for students to sort, count, and compare groups of up to 10 objects. Goals: Determine the number of objects, within 20, and represent the quantity with a written number. | Use the words “more” and “fewer” to compare (orally) groups of objects within 20.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l2, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L2",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 2: Count and Compare Collections. The purpose of this lesson is for students to count and compare collections of up to 20 objects. Goals: Choose methods for counting and representing a group of objects. | Compare and contrast (orally) methods for organizing and counting a group of objects.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l3, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L3",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 3: Count to Add and Subtract. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use their knowledge of the count sequence to solve story problems about adding or subtracting 1. Goals: Explain (orally) strategies for solving story problems about adding or taking away 1 within 10, including strategies based on the count sequence.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l4, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L4",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 4: 1 More and 1 Less. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use their knowledge of the count sequence to determine 1 more and 1 less than a number or a group of objects. Goals: Explain (orally) strategies for determining “1 more” or “1 less” than a given number. | Generalize (orally) that adding 1 more results in the next number in the count sequence and taking away 1 results in the previous number in the count sequence.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l5, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L5",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 5: Order Numbers 1–20. The purpose of this lesson is for students to put numbers 1–20 in order and use their knowledge of the count sequence to identify 1 more or 1 less than a given number. Goals: Explain (orally) strategies for ordering numbers 1–20.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l6, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L6",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 6: Create Number Books (Part 1). The purpose of this lesson is for students to use numbers to represent objects in their environment. Goals: Identify and represent, including with written numbers, quantities in the school community.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l7, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L7",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 7: Create Number Books (Part 2). The purpose of this lesson is for students to use numbers to represent objects in their environment. Goals: Create drawings to represent a group of objects in the school community and represent the group with a written number.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l8, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L8",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 8: Find Someone Who, Find Something That. The purpose of this lesson is for students to answer mathematical questions about their classmates and community. Goals: Answer mathematical questions about their community.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l9, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L9",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 9: Where’s the Math?. The purpose of this lesson is for students to ask and answer mathematical questions about their school community. Goals: Ask and answer (orally) mathematical questions about the classroom community.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l10, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L10",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 10: Tell Stories about Our School. The purpose of this lesson is for students to develop story problems about their school community. Goals: Create (orally) story problems about the school community.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l11, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L11",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 11: Share Story Problems. The purpose of this lesson is for students to represent and solve story problems about their school community. Goals: Present (orally) strategies for solving story problems about the school community.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l12, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L12",
