standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l13, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L13",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 13: Dominoes to 5. The purpose of this lesson is for students to develop fluency with adding and subtracting within 5 as they identify compositions and decompositions of numbers to 5. Goals: Describe (orally) compositions and decompositions of numbers within 5 and represent the parts with an expression. | Use “more,” “fewer,” and “the same number” to compare (orally) numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l14, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L14",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 14: Sort and Color Expressions and Images within 5. The purpose of this lesson is for students to develop fluency with adding and subtracting within 5. Goals: Interpret drawings showing addition and subtraction strategies. | Match (orally) different addition and subtraction expressions that represent the same value.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l15, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L15",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 15: Addition and Subtraction Expressions within 5. The purpose of this lesson is for students to develop fluency with adding and subtracting within 5. Goals: Explain (orally) methods for identifying the value of addition and subtraction expressions. | Explain (orally) strategies for comparing addition and subtraction expressions.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l16, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L16",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 16: Parts to Make 5. The purpose of this lesson is for students to develop fluency with adding and subtracting within 5. Goals: Explain (orally) strategies for identifying the unknown value to make a given total.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l17, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L17",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 17: Make and Break Apart 10. The purpose of this lesson is for students to compose and decompose 10 in multiple ways. Goals: Use equation frames to generate equations that represent decompositions of 10. | Use objects to represent different decompositions of 10 written as equations.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l18, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L18",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 18: All the Ways to Make 10. The purpose of this lesson is for students to find all of the compositions and decompositions of 10 in the context of a story problem. Goals: Choose strategies to solve related Put Together, Result Unknown and Put Together/Take Apart, Both Addends Unknown problems. | Represent all the ways to compose and decompose 10 to solve a Put Together/Take Apart, Both Addends Unknown problem.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l19, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L19",
    "IM Kindergarten Unit 8 Lesson 19: Find the Number That Makes 10. The purpose of this lesson is for students to find the number that makes 10 when added to a given number. Goals: Explain (orally) strategies for determining a number that makes 10 when added to a given number, and express the composition with an equation.").
standard_anchor(im_kindergarten_u8_l20, im_lesson, "IM-GK-U8-L20",
