standard_anchor(im_grade5_u3_l5, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U3-L5",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 3 Lesson 5: Multiply a Unit Fraction by a Non-Unit Fraction. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use diagrams and expressions to calculate the product of a unit fraction and a non-unit fraction. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies to determine the product of a unit fraction and a non-unit fraction. | Represent the product of a unit fraction and a non- unit fraction with diagrams and expressions and interpret (orally and in writing) the representations.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u3_l6, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U3-L6",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 3 Lesson 6: Multiply Fractions. The purpose of this lesson is for students to calculate areas of rectangles where both side lengths are non-unit fractions. Goals: Determine the product of 2 non-unit fractions represented by a diagram. | Represent a diagram with a multiplication expression involving 2 non-unit fractions and interpret (orally and in writing) the expression.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u3_l7, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U3-L7",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 3 Lesson 7: Generalize Fraction Multiplication. The purpose of this lesson is to generalize strategies for calculating products of fractions. Goals: Calculate the product of 2 fractions. | Generalize (orally and in writing) that                .").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u3_l8, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U3-L8",
