standard_anchor(im_grade5_u3_l19, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U3-L19",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 3 Lesson 19: Fraction Games. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use their understanding of fractions and division to make the largest and smallest expressions using given numbers. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for creating multiplication and division expressions with given whole numbers and unit fractions that result in the greatest or least product or quotient.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u3_l20, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U3-L20",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 3 Lesson 20: Recipes and Fractions. The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply what they’ve learned about multiplying and dividing fractions to solve problems related to recipes. Goals: Ask (orally and in writing) mathematical questions about a situation involving fractions. | Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for solving problems involving multiplication and division of fractions in a context.").
