standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l1, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L1",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 1: Estimate and Find Products. The purpose of this lesson is for students to make estimates and calculations of products. Goals: Describe (orally and using other representations) strategies for multiplying a two-digit number by a one-digit number, by a two-digit number, and by a three-digit number. | Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for estimating the product of a two-digit number and a three-dig").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l2, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L2",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 2: Partial Products in Diagrams. The purpose of this lesson is for students to multiply multi-digit whole numbers, using strategies based on place value and the properties of operations. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) diagrams that represent the product of a two-digit number and a three-digit number. | Label diagrams to represent the product of a two- digit number and a three-digit number and calculate the value.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l3, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L3",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 3: Partial Products in Algorithms. The purpose of this lesson is for students to multiply multi-digit whole numbers, using partial products. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) different ways to record partial products for a three-digit number multiplied by a two-digit number. | Match expressions with diagrams to show how partial products can be used to multiply a three-digit number by a two-digit number.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l4, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L4",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 4: Standard Algorithm: One-digit and Multi-digit Numbers, with Composing. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use the standard algorithm to multiply up to five-digit numbers by one-digit numbers. Goals: Calculate the product of a one-digit number and a multi-digit number, using the standard algorithm. | Interpret (orally and in writing) the steps in a worked example, calculating the product of a one-digit number and a multi-digit number, and critique (orally) an interpretation.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l5, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L5",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 5: Standard Algorithm: Multi-digit Numbers, without Composing. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use the standard algorithm to multiply up to three-digit numbers by two- digit numbers, without composing a new unit. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) how using partial products relates to using the standard algorithm when multiplying a three-digit number by a two-digit number. | Use the standard algorithm to multiply three-digit numbers by two-digit numbers, without composing new units.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l6, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L6",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 6: Standard Algorithm: Multi-digit Numbers, with Composing. The purpose of this lesson is for students to understand and apply the standard algorithm for multiplication when multiplying three-digit numbers by two-digit numbers, with composition of new units. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) the steps in the standard algorithm used to multiply a three-digit number by a two-digit number, with composing new units. | Use the standard algorithm to multiply three-digit numbers by two-digit numbers, with composing new units.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l7, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L7",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 7: Build Multiplication Fluency. The purpose of this lesson is to multiply three-digit numbers by two-digit numbers, with any number of newly composed units. Goals: Create and solve three-digit-number-by-two-digit- number multiplication problems, the products of which meet given criteria. | Explain (orally) how the digits in each factor affect the product of a two-digit number and three-digit number.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l8, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L8",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 8: The Birds. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use whole-number multiplication to solve problems. Goals: Explain (orally) strategies for estimating the products of multi-digit numbers in a context. | Explain (orally) strategies for multiplying multi-digit numbers in a context.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l9, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L9",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 9: World’s Record Folk Dance. The purpose of this lesson is for students to estimate and solve multi-digit division problems in a way that makes sense to them. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for dividing a multi-digit number by a one-digit number. | Represent a division situation, with an expression.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l10, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L10",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 10: Different Partial Quotients. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use place-value understanding and the relationship between multiplication and division to divide multi-digit numbers. Goals: Determine how to decompose the quotient that results from dividing a three-digit number by a two- digit number into smaller quotients. | Identify and interpret (orally) expressions that show partial quotients for dividing a three-digit number by a two-digit number.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l11, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L11",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 11: A Partial-Quotients Algorithm. The purpose of this lesson is for students to learn a partial-quotients algorithm to divide multi-digit numbers by two- digit numbers. Goals: Describe (orally and in writing) the steps used to divide a three-digit number by a two-digit number, with partial quotients, and critique (orally) a description.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l12, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L12",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 12: Divide, Using Partial Quotients. The purpose of this lesson is for students to deepen their understanding of a partial-quotients algorithm and use it to divide up to four-digit dividends by two-digit divisors. Goals: Calculate the quotients of three-digit numbers divided by two-digit numbers, and explain (orally and in writing) the strategies used. | Explain (orally and in writing) the strategies for determining if a quotient is reasonable.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l13, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L13",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 13: Practice a Partial-Quotients Algorithm. The purpose of this lesson is for students to practice using a partial-quotients algorithm. Goals: Describe (orally and in writing) the errors in a division calculation, using partial quotients. | Divide up to four-digit dividends by two-digit divisors, and compare and contrast (orally) the strategies used.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l14, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L14",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 14: Find Unknown Side Lengths. The purpose of this lesson is for students to find unknown side lengths of rectangles and rectangular prisms, using their understanding of area, volume, and multi-digit division. Goals: Use the relationship between multiplication and division to solve problems involving area and volume, and explain (orally) the strategies used.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l15, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L15",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 15: World’s Record Noodle Soup. The purpose of this lesson is for students to estimate and solve multi-digit division with mixed-number quotients. Goals: Critique (orally and in writing) an estimate for a multi-digit division problem. | Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for estimating the quotient of multi-digit numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l16, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L16",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 16: Fractions as Partial Quotients. The purpose of this lesson is for students to interpret sums of fractions as partial quotients. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) a sum of fractions as a decomposition of a multi-digit division problem into smaller quotients. | Use a decomposition of a multi-digit division problem, represented as a sum of fractions, to determine the quotient.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l17, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L17",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 17: A Lot of Milk. The purpose of this lesson is to estimate products and quotients, using a volume context. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for estimating products and quotients of multi-digit numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l18, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L18",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 18: Trash Talk. The purpose of this lesson is to find areas by multiplying side lengths in situations in which the side lengths are two- or three-digit numbers. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for estimating whether a distance is more than, about the same as, or less than a kilometer. | Use multiplication and division of multi-digit numbers to solve problems involving area, and explain (orally and in writing) the reasoning use").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l19, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L19",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 19: Shipping Trash. The purpose of this lesson is to estimate and calculate products and quotients of whole numbers in order to understand the volume of recyclable plastic the United States ships abroad each year. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for solving real-world problems involving multiplication and division of multi-digit numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u4_l20, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U4-L20",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 4 Lesson 20: Food-Waste Journal. The purpose of this lesson is for students to estimate and calculate products and quotients of whole numbers in order to understand the amount of food waste that is produced in the United States each year. Goals: Determine information needed, and justify (orally and in writing) assumptions made, to solve real- world problems involving multiplication and division of multi-digit numbers.").
%   Unit 5
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l1, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L1",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 1: What Is a Thousandth?. The purpose of this lesson is for students to recognize the unit of thousandths in relationship to tenths and hundredths. Goals: Comprehend (in spoken language) the meaning of “one-thousandth” and that it can be represented in writing as       or 0.001. | Interpret (orally and in writing) diagrams that represent 0.1, 0.01, and 0.001.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l2, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L2",
