standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l3, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L3",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 3: Thousandths in Expanded Form. The purpose of this lesson is for students to represent decimals to the thousandths place in expanded form. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) different representations of a decimal and describe (orally) how they relate. | Represent decimals to thousandths in decimal notation, in expanded form, as fractions, with diagrams, and with words.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l4, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L4",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 4: Explore Place Value Relationships. The purpose of this lesson is for students to explore the relationships between different ways of representing a decimal using the context of weights and a balance. Goals: Describe (orally and in writing) relationships between tenths, hundredths, and thousandths. | Generalize (orally and in writing) that a digit in one place in a decimal number represents 10 times as much as the same digit in the place to its right and as much as the same digit in").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l5, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L5",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 5: Compare Decimals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use place value understanding to compare decimals to the thousandths place. Goals: Explain (using words and other representations) strategies for comparing decimal to thousandths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l6, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L6",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 6: Compare Decimals on the Number Line. The purpose of this lesson is for students to represent decimals to the thousandths place on the number line and compare them. Goals: Represent decimals on a number line. | Use a number line to compare decimals and represent the comparison using the symbols >, <, or =.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l7, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L7",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 7: Round Doubloons. The purpose of this lesson is for students to examine situations where decimal quantities are rounded. Goals: Comprehend (in spoken and written language) what it means to measure to the “nearest” whole, tenth, or hundredth of a unit. | Use understanding of decimal place value and rounding to justify (orally and in writing) conclusions made about measurements.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l8, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L8",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 8: Round Decimals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to round to the nearest whole, tenth, and hundredth. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for rounding decimal numbers to the nearest whole number, tenth, and hundredth. | Use place value understanding to label a number line and estimate the location of a decimal to thousandths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l9, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L9",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 9: Order Decimals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to order decimals. Goals: Determine the correct order of decimals and explain (orally) the strategy used. | Identify a decimal between 2 given decimals to thousandths and justify (orally) the identification.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l10, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L10",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 10: Solve Problems with Decimals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to round and order decimals to the nearest one, tenth, and hundredth. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) the impact of rounding decimals in a context.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l11, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L11",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 11: Make Sense of Decimal Addition. The purpose of this lesson is for students to add decimals in a way that makes sense to them. Goals: Describe (orally and using other representations) strategies for adding decimal numbers to hundredths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l12, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L12",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 12: Estimate and Add. The purpose of this lesson is for students to estimate and find the value of addition expressions with decimals. Goals: Describe (orally and in writing) the steps in a worked example of the standard algorithm for adding decimals to hundredths. | Use place value strategies to estimate and calculate the sum of decimals to hundredths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l13, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L13",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 13: Analyze Addition Mistakes. The purpose of this lesson is for students to add decimals and consider common errors in lining up place values when adding with the standard algorithm. Goals: Critique (orally and in writing) calculations of a sum of decimals to hundredths using the standard algorithm. | Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for adding decimal to hundredths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l14, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L14",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 14: Make Sense of Decimal Subtraction. The purpose of this lesson is for students to subtract decimals to the hundredths place in a way that makes sense to them. Goals: Describe (orally and using other representations) strategies for subtracting decimals to hundredths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l15, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L15",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 15: Estimate and Subtract. The purpose of this lesson is for students to estimate and find the value of subtraction expressions with decimals. Goals: Describe (orally and in writing) the steps in a worked example of the standard algorithm for subtracting decimals to hundredths. | Use place value strategies to estimate and calculate the difference of decimals to hundredths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l16, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L16",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 16: Addition and Subtraction. The purpose of this lesson is for students to add and subtract decimals. Goals: Calculate sums and differences of decimals to hundredths and explain (orally and in writing) strategies used.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l17, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L17",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 17: Multiply Decimals and Whole Numbers. The purpose of this lesson is for students to multiply a whole number by any amount of tenths or hundredths. Goals: Describe (orally and using other representations) strategies for multiplying a 1-digit whole number and a decimal number with 1 non-zero digit.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l18, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L18",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 18: Use Whole Number Facts. The purpose of this lesson is for students to multiply a whole number and a decimal using their understanding of properties of operations and place value. Goals: Identify and interpret diagrams and expressions (orally and in writing) that represent the product of a whole number and a decimal number.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l19, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L19",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 19: Use Properties to Multiply Decimals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to interpret and find the value of multiplication expressions with decimals and whole numbers. Goals: Calculate products of a whole number and a decimal with 2 non-zero digits and explain (orally and in writing) strategies used. | Match decimal multiplication expressions that have equivalent values and justify (orally) the matches.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l20, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L20",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 20: Products in the Hundredths Place. The purpose of this lesson is for students to find products of tenths and tenths. Goals: Calculate the product of 2 decimals to tenths and explain (orally and in writing) strategies used. | Critique (orally and in writing) a given product of 2 decimals to tenths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l21, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L21",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 21: Multiply More Decimals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use place value understanding and multi-digit whole number products to find multi-digit decimal products. Goals: Calculate the product of 2 decimals to hundredths and explain (orally) strategies used. | Justify (orally and in writing) that the product of 2 decimals is equivalent to the product of 2 whole numbers and a power of 10.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l22, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L22",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 22: Divide Whole Numbers by 0.1 and 0.01. The purpose of this lesson is for students to notice and explain patterns when dividing a whole number by one tenth and one hundredth. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for dividing a whole number by 0.1 or 0.01 and critique (orally) explanations. | Generalize (orally and in writing) that dividing a whole number by 0.1 is equivalent to multiplying it by 10, and dividing a whole number by 0.01 is equival").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l23, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L23",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 23: Divide Whole Numbers by Decimals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to divide a whole number by a decimal less than 1 by reasoning about the number of groups of one tenth or one hundredth in one whole. Goals: Calculate quotients of a whole number divided by 0.2 or 0.02 and explain (orally and in writing) strategies used. | Interpret (orally and in writing) diagrams and expressions that represent dividing a whole number by 0.2 or 0.02.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l24, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L24",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 24: Divide Decimals by Whole Numbers. The purpose of this lesson is for students to divide a decimal less than 1 by a whole number. Goals: Calculate quotients of a decimal to the hundredths divided by a whole number and explain (orally and in writing) strategies used.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l25, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L25",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 25: Divide Decimals by Decimals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to divide decimals greater than 1 by decimals less than 1. Goals: Calculate quotients of a decimal divided by 0.1 or 0.01 and explain (orally and in writing) strategies used. | Interpret (orally and in writing) diagrams that represent dividing a decimal by 0.1 or 0.01.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u5_l26, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U5-L26",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 5 Lesson 26: Book Fair. The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply their understanding of working with decimal numbers in a real-world context. Goals: Determine assumptions needed to solve problems involving decimals to hundredths in a context. | Solve problems involving the four operations with decimals to the hundredths in a context and explain (orally and in writing) strategies used.").
%   Unit 6
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l1, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L1",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 1: Place-Value Patterns. The purpose of this lesson is for students to observe place-value patterns when multiplying and dividing. Goals: Generalize (orally) that in a multi-digit number, a digit in one place represents 10 times as much as it represents in the place to its right and       of what it represents in the place to its left.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l2, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L2",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 2: Powers of 10. The purpose of this lesson is for students to recognize exponential notation for powers of 10 and to use exponential notation to represent large numbers. Goals: Use exponential notation to represent large powers of 10.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l3, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L3",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 3: Metric Conversion and Multiplication by Powers of 10. The purpose of this lesson is for students to convert from a larger metric length unit to a smaller metric length unit. Students observe patterns when different numbers are multiplied by 10, by 100, or by 1,000. Goals: Generalize (orally and in writing) the factor needed to convert from a larger metric length unit to a smaller metric length unit.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l4, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L4",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 4: Metric Conversion and Division by Powers of 10. The purpose of this lesson is for students to convert from a smaller metric length unit to a larger metric length unit, using a context of track and field. Students observe patterns when different numbers are divided by 10, by 100, or by 1, Goals: Determine (orally and in writing) the quotient of a decimal number and 10, 100, or 1,000. | Generalize (orally and in writing) the divisor needed to convert from a smaller metric length unit to a larger metric length unit.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l5, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L5",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 5: Multi-step Conversion Problems: Metric Lengths. The purpose of this lesson is for students to solve multi-step conversion problems about distance in metric units. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for solving problems that require the conversion of metric units of length.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l6, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L6",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 6: Multi-step Conversion Problems: Metric Liquid Volumes. The purpose of this lesson is for students to solve conversion problems, using metric volume units. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for solving problems that require the conversion of metric units of volume.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l7, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L7",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 7: Multi-step Conversion Problems: Customary Lengths. The purpose of this lesson is for students to solve problems involving customary length units. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for solving problems that require the conversion of customary units of length.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l8, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L8",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 8: Add and Subtract Fractions. The purpose of this lesson is for students to add and subtract fractions with unlike denominators in ways that make sense to them. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for adding and subtracting fractions with unlike denominators when one denominator is a multiple of the other.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l9, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L9",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 9: Use Expressions with the Same Value. The purpose of this lesson is for students to add and subtract fractions with unlike denominators by replacing the given expressions with equivalent expressions with common denominators. Goals: Compare and contrast (orally and in writing) strategies for adding and subtracting fractions with unlike denominators when one denominator is a multiple of the other.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l10, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L10",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 10: All Sorts of Denominators. The purpose of this lesson is for students to explain why it is possible to find a common denominator of two given fractions by multiplying the denominators. Goals: Explain (orally) strategies for adding and subtracting fractions with unlike denominators when one is not a multiple of the other.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l11, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L11",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 11: Different Ways to Subtract. The purpose of this lesson is for students to subtract fractions with unlike denominators, including mixed numbers. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for subtracting mixed numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l12, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L12",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 12: Solve Problems. The purpose of this lesson is for students to solve problems that involve adding and subtracting fractions with unlike denominators. Goals: Interpret and add and subtract fractions and mixed numbers in context.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l13, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L13",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 13: Put It All Together: Add and Subtract Fractions. The purpose of this lesson is for students to consider different denominators they can use to add or subtract fractions. Goals: Critique (orally and in writing) different choices for a common denominator of two fractions. | Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for adding and subtracting fractions and mixed numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l14, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L14",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 14: Representing Fractions on a Line Plot. The purpose of this lesson is for students to make and interpret line plots displaying fractions in eighths. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) and create line plots with fractions and mixed numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l15, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L15",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 15: Problem Solving with Line Plots. The purpose of this lesson is for students to make line plots and to solve problems, using the data. Goals: Determine the information needed to answer questions about a line plot with fractions and mixed numbers. Ask (orally) questions to elicit that information.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l16, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L16",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 16: Compare Products. The purpose of this lesson is for students to compare the size of a product to the size of one factor, using a strategy that makes sense to them. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for comparing          with its factor , when is a fraction and is a whole number.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l17, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L17",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 17: Interpret Diagrams. The purpose of this lesson is for students to compare the size of a product to the size of one factor on the basis of the size of the other factor, without performing the indicated multiplication. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for ordering and         when, and are fractions and is a whole number.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l18, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L18",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 18: Compare without Multiplying. The purpose of this lesson is for students to compare the size of a product to the size of one factor, based on the size of the other factor. Goals: Justify (orally and in writing) why           if        , and               if       , when is a fraction and is a whole number.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l19, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L19",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 19: Compare to 1. Goals: Justify (orally and in writing) why             if      , and               if        when, and      are fractions.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l20, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L20",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 20: Will It Always Work?. The purpose of this lesson is for students to explain how the product of two numbers compares to one factor based on the size of the other factor. Goals: Generalize (orally and in writing) that             if , and              if       , for any rational numbers and .").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u6_l21, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U6-L21",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 6 Lesson 21: Weekend Investigation. The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply their understanding of making line plots and using operations with fractions to analyze data. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) information in a line plot that represents fractional data. | Present fractional data on a line plot.").
%   Unit 7
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l1, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L1",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 1: Explore the Coordinate Grid. The purpose of this lesson is for students to build familiarity with the structure of the coordinate grid. Goals: Ask (orally) questions to identify a specific shape on a coordinate grid. | Describe (orally) a shape on a coordinate grid.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l2, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L2",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 2: Points on the Coordinate Grid. The purpose of this lesson is for students to locate and describe points on the coordinate grid. Goals: Compare and contrast (orally) points on a coordinate grid. | Determine the coordinates of a point in a coordinate grid.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l3, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L3",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 3: Plot More Points. The purpose of this lesson is for students to plot points on the coordinate grid and recognize the importance of attending to precision when naming coordinates. Goals: Draw and label points in the coordinate plane. | Generalize (orally and in writing) that when two points have the same first (second) coordinate, they lie on the same vertical (resp. horizontal) line.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l4, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L4",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 4: Sort Quadrilaterals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to sort quadrilaterals and begin to notice the hierarchy and subcategories of quadrilaterals. Goals: Ask (orally) questions to identify a specific quadrilateral. | Determine attributes of rectangles, rhombuses, squares, trapezoids, and parallelograms.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l5, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L5",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 5: Trapezoids. The purpose of this lesson is for students to explore two different definitions of trapezoid. Goals: Describe (orally and in writing) attributes of trapezoids. | Explain (orally and in writing) the relationship between trapezoids and other types of quadrilaterals.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l6, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L6",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 6: Hierarchy of Quadrilaterals. The purpose of this lesson is for students to continue to build the hierarchy of quadrilaterals. Students use categories and subcategories to see that if a shape is a square it is also a rhombus and also a parallelogram. Goals: Compare and contrast (orally and in writing) two different quadrilaterals with the same perimeter. | Critique (orally and in writing) a claim about the relationship between squares and rhombuses.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l7, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L7",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 7: Rectangles and Squares. The purpose of this lesson is for students to understand that a square is also a rectangle. Goals: Determine the relationships between rectangles, rhombuses, squares, trapezoids, and parallelograms.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l8, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L8",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 8: Sort Triangles. The purpose of this lesson is for students to classify triangles using angle measures and side lengths. Goals: Describe (orally and in writing) attributes of right triangles. | Match triangles based on given attributes.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l9, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L9",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 9: Generate Patterns. The purpose of this lesson is for students to generate patterns, given two rules, and identify relationships between corresponding terms in the different patterns. Goals: Generalize (orally and in writing) the relationship between two sequences generated from additive rules. | Use additive rules to determine a sequence of values.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l10, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L10",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 10: Interpret Relationships. The purpose of this lesson is for students to generate patterns based on two given rules and then identify and explain more complex relationships. Goals: Critique (orally and in writing) a claim about the relationship between two sequences generated from additive rules.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l11, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L11",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 11: Patterns and Ordered Pairs. The purpose of this lesson is for students to represent corresponding terms in two patterns on the coordinate grid. Goals: Draw the graph of a set of coordinate pairs. | Use additive rules to determine coordinates for points in the plane.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l12, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L12",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 12: Represent Problems on the Coordinate Grid. The purpose of this lesson is for students to represent situations by plotting and interpreting points on the coordinate grid. Goals: Interpret (orally and in writing) the coordinates of a point in context. | Represent information about a context as a point in the coordinate plane.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l13, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L13",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 13: Perimeter and Area of Rectangles. The purpose of this lesson is for students to examine rectangles with a given perimeter or area, and plot their length and width on the coordinate grid. Goals: Represent the relationship between the length and width of a rectangle with a fixed area (or perimeter) in the coordinate plane.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u7_l14, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U7-L14",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 7 Lesson 14: Copies of Figures. The purpose of this lesson is for students to use what they’ve learned about coordinate grids to make a copy of a figure. Goals: Use a coordinate grid to make a copy of a figure.").
%   Unit 8
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l1, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L1",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 1: Find the Greatest Product. The purpose of this lesson is for students to recognize and explain place-value patterns as they find products using the standard algorithm they learned in Unit 4. Goals: Justify (orally and in writing) why a product of two numbers formed from a given set of digits is as large as possible.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l2, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L2",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 2: More Multiplication. The purpose of this lesson is for students to practice using the standard algorithm to multiply multi-digit numbers. Goals: Calculate the product of two multi-digit whole numbers. | Critique (orally and in writing) a calculation of the product of two multi-digit whole numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l3, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L3",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 3: Factors as a Factor in Our Strategy Choice. The purpose of this lesson is for students to reason about how the factors in a problem can influence the strategy they use to find the product, in particular identifying cases where the standard algorithm would be useful. Goals: Choose a strategy for multiplying and justify (orally and in writing) the choice. | Use the standard algorithm to fluently multiply multi- digit whole numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l4, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L4",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 4: Dive Back into Division. The purpose of this lesson is for students to estimate and find whole-number quotients with up to four-digit dividends and two-digit divisors. Goals: Estimate and calculate the quotient of multi-digit whole numbers. | Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for finding different pairs of numbers with the same given quotient.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l5, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L5",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 5: More Division. The purpose of this lesson is for students to find whole-number quotients of whole numbers with up to four-digit dividends and two-digit divisors, using strategies based on place value, the properties of operations, and the relationship bet Goals: Critique (orally and in writing) a calculation of the quotient of two multi-digit whole numbers. | Explain (orally) a strategy for determining the quotient of two multi-digit whole numbers.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l6, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L6",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 6: Revisit Volume. The purpose of this lesson is for students to solve real-world problems about volume. Goals: Determine a set of dimensions for a rectangular prism with a given volume. | Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for estimating the volume of a tall building.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l7, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L7",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 7: Estimate the Volume of the World’s Largest Wagon. The purpose of this lesson is for students to solve problems involving volume. Students multiply and divide multi-digit whole numbers using the algorithms learned in the previous sections. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for estimating the volume of a real-world object.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l8, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L8",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 8: Fill the World's Largest Wagon. The purpose of this lesson is for students to solve problems involving volume. Students multiply and divide multi-digit whole numbers using the algorithms learned in the previous sections. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for solving multi-step volume problems in context.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l9, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L9",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 9: Problem Solving with Volume: Water. The purpose of this lesson is for students to solve real-world problems about volume. Goals: Explain (orally and in writing) strategies for solving multi-step volume problems in context.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l10, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L10",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 10: Here Comes the Sum. The purpose of this lesson is for students to practice adding fractions with unlike denominators. Goals: Add fractions with unlike denominators.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l11, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L11",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 11: What’s the Difference?. The purpose of this lesson is for students to practice subtracting fractions with unlike denominators. Goals: Subtract fractions and mixed numbers with unlike denominators.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l12, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L12",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 12: Decimal Game Day. The purpose of this lesson is for students to practice adding decimals. Goals: Add decimals to hundredths.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l13, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L13",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 13: Multiply Fractions Game Day. The purpose of this lesson is for students to practice multiplying fractions. Goals: Multiply a fraction or whole number by a fraction.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l14, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L14",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 14: Notice and Wonder. The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply their understanding of fractions as division to create a Notice and Wonder activity. Goals: Create (in writing) and present a Notice and Wonder activity.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l15, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L15",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 15: Estimation Exploration. The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply their understanding of multi-digit multiplication and the standard algorithm of multiplication to create an Estimation Exploration activity. Goals: Create (in writing) and present an Estimation Exploration activity.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l16, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L16",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 16: Number Talk. The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply their understanding of dividing multi-digit whole numbers to create a Number Talk activity. Goals: Create a Number Talk activity. | Describe (orally) how a set of expressions are related.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l17, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L17",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 17: True or False?. The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply their understanding of adding and subtracting fractions with unlike denominators to create a True or False? activity. Goals: Create a True or False? activity involving addition and subtraction equations with fractions.").
standard_anchor(im_grade5_u8_l18, im_lesson, "IM-G5-U8-L18",
    "IM Grade5 Unit 8 Lesson 18: Which Three Go Together?. The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply their understanding of volume to create a Which Three Go Together? activity. Goals: Create (in writing) a Which Three Go Together? activity.").

